*JUST IGNORE THIS BRANCH FOR A WHILE*

So I found the bug, pretty sure its an issue with the fact that we call entire classes rather than instances of the classes, meaning we can't alter them. They're basically static. Problem is I'm still figuring out how to make them proper objects and I have other things to do, so I'm just leaving this commit here to come back to with context.

*DONT PUSH TO MASTER AS-IS*

I made the change that psuhes the userinput to the innertables, which is good. Problem is that this let me discover that we have a bug where updates to the userinput don't get passed all the way down. Not sure if in resultTable or innerTable, I think its innerTable. I'm gonna strart looking there, but I don't plan to look too long, I just was trying to get the updated innertables in place.
